author: Inside Edition
description: Former president Joe Biden appeared to have a large gash on his head when greeting supporters. Fred Karger, who recorded the video in Rehoboth Beach, Delaware, spoke with Inside Edition. He says the wound, to his eye, looked like the aftermath of skin cancer surgery. Inside Edition showed the video to dermatologist Dr. Doris Day. Biden has dealt with skin cancer before. In 2023, he had a basal cell carcinoma removed from his chest. He is currently battling stage four prostate cancer.
title: Joe Biden Appears to Have Large Gash on Head

author: Inside Edition
description: Kids posting their skincare routines on social media are going viral. Although the products are sold legally, dermatologists that INSIDE EDITION spoke to say that some of these skincare products may be inappropriate for some young girls’ skin. INSIDE EDITION collaborated with CBS California Investigative Correspondent Julie Watts for this special report.
title: Are Some Kids Using Beauty Products That Could Be Harmful to Their skin?

author: Inside Edition
description: Famed Italian fashion designer Giorgio Armani has died. His company released a statement announcing his passing Thursday. He's credited with creating the power suit and has dressed some of the most famous people in the world. Armani is being celebrated as a fashion powerhouse, his name becoming a symbol of Italian elegance and style, but the man himself was known not only for his talent, but his business acumen. Giorgio Armani was 91. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Iconic Italian Fashion Designer Giorgio Armani Dies at 91

author: Inside Edition
description: What is a shark without its bite? According to scientists, it's more dangerous than a shark with a full set of working chompers. Researchers in Germany say they're seeing a disturbing trend – rising acid levels in sea water are eroding sharks' teeth. They say it's making it harder for them to hunt and ultimately survive, and that has implications for the rest of the world. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Scientists Say Sharks are Losing Teeth and That's Not Good

author: Inside Edition
description: Police raced into Chick-Fil-A at seven in the morning, but it wasn't the scene of a crime. They were looking for a hungry 5-year-old who was craving a Chick-Fil-A breakfast so badly, he snuck out of the house. The manager called the police. The boy's name is William and he strolled to the restaurant barefoot. An officer asked the boy where his house was and brought him home. His parents answered the door shocked and were thankful their hungry boy was home safe.
title: Barefoot 5-Year-Old Sneaks Out of House to Chick-Fil-A for Breakfast
